00:13:52,440 --> 00:13:56,800
They gave us an amazing testimonial, and then they became Cleo evangelists.

215
00:13:56,800 --> 00:14:03,280
But also, in the background, we were recording those calls to make sure that we spotted patterns in thinking,

216
00:14:03,280 --> 00:14:09,240
in problems, in bugs, in issues that people were having so we could actually fix them immediately.

217
00:14:09,240 --> 00:14:15,160
So, it was also an iteration play for us so we could have the best product available as fast as possible.

218
00:14:15,160 --> 00:14:21,240
So then, step number five, what you need to also do is think about how can you get the most demand as fast as possible?

219
00:14:21,240 --> 00:14:29,400
You build your waitlist, and then to incentivize customers to buy, you offer them a lifetime discount or something that feels exclusive.

220
00:14:29,400 --> 00:14:31,240
You're trying to push someone to buy.

221
00:14:31,240 --> 00:14:32,880
And there's many ways to do it.

222
00:14:32,880 --> 00:14:37,320
With psychology, you can do it through curiosity, you could do it through scarcity, or you could do it through FOMO.

223
00:14:37,320 --> 00:14:40,959
We tried all of them, but the one that worked best at the start was scarcity.

224
00:14:40,959 --> 00:14:46,800
We told people we only have 500 spots available, which made people want to take action faster.

225
00:14:46,800 --> 00:14:50,600
When something's available so easily, people don't want to buy it immediately.

226
00:14:50,600 --> 00:14:54,680
So, you need to add that incentive for people to go in and buy and also feel exclusive.

227
00:14:54,680 --> 00:14:58,640
And also, if you want to add something else, you can offer them a lifetime discount,

228
00:14:58,640 --> 00:14:59,480
which is what we did.

229
00:14:59,480 --> 00:15:01,880
We told them this is 50% off for a lifetime.

230
00:15:01,880 --> 00:15:05,720
If you buy now, you will never have to pay the newer price ever again.

231
00:15:05,720 --> 00:15:08,560
And then, number six, you need to nurture your customers.

232
00:15:08,560 --> 00:15:13,160
Most people just launch things and they forget about them and then just, you know, go celebrate the MRR.

233
00:15:13,160 --> 00:15:18,920
What we're doing actively at Cleo is we're keeping in touch closely with every single one of our customers.

234
00:15:18,920 --> 00:15:26,079
One of our co-founders, Rob, he's literally given his personal number to every single one of our users so they can make sure that they're using the tool right,

235
00:15:26,079 --> 00:15:27,280
that they feel supported.

236
00:15:27,280 --> 00:15:32,480
Most people don't do that, but the thing is you need to be doing the things that don't scale if you want to scale faster.

237
00:15:32,480 --> 00:15:37,200
So, if I was starting over all over from scratch, that's exactly what I would do.

